\b 2) What is EBS?\par
\tab\b0 EBS stands for Elastic Block Store\par
\tab  it is a cloud-based storage service that allows you to store data in a highly reliable and durable way.it enables you to create & manage storage volumes that you can attach to your ec2 instance.\par
\tab EBS volumes are designed for high durability, and they use redundant storage across multiple availability zones to ensure data availability in the event of a failure. EBS volumes also provide features such as encryption, snapshots, and automated backup to help ensure the security and recoverability of data stored in EBS volumes.\par
